  <Group id = "grp_Techskills1"  backimage="~/Images/back.png" nextimage="~/Images/next.png">
    <Separator>
      <b>Page 3 of 5: Your technique skills:</b>
    </Separator>
    <Question id="P7" type="mcss" layout="vertical" required="true">
      <Statement>
        <b>You’ve just been given a complex task to code. What are you most likely to do?</b>
      </Statement>
      <Responses>
        <Response id="A1">Get straight into the task by putting in the initial code and prototyping the task.</Response>
        <Response id="A2">Get everyone’s feedback on the problem, discuss all the possible options, then decide the best way to approach the problem given the current situation.</Response>
      </Responses>
    </Question>
    <Question id="P8" type="mcss" layout="vertical" required="true">
      <Statement>
        <b>Who is a ‘better’ programmer?</b>
      </Statement>
      <Responses>
        <Response id="A1">Someone who went to university/college and has at least a masters in their field. They should read as many books on a subject as they can find before starting on it.</Response>
        <Response id="A2">Someone who has been coding since they were 5 and simply goes by raw talent alone.</Response>
      </Responses>
    </Question>
    <Question id="P9" type="mcss" layout="vertical" required="true">
      <Statement>
        <b>The ‘perfect’ language will:</b>
      </Statement>
      <Responses>
        <Response id="A1">Allow anybody in the world to program.</Response>
        <Response id="A2">Allow me to make the best use of systems resources.</Response>
      </Responses>
    </Question>
  </Group>

